cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this library in research, write-ups, or production GTM work, please cite it as below."
title: "AI GTM Skill Library"
abstract: >-
  A library of 31 opinionated go-to-market skills for Claude Code and GitHub
  Copilot. Each skill is a self-contained Markdown specification that encodes
  a named mnemonic framework, an applied process, an output specification,
  and a list of paired skills. Covers the GTM lifecycle (discover, design,
  position, amplify, launch, optimize) plus a RevOps cluster (customer
  success, analytics, advocacy, lead nurture, loyalty, referral, renewal,
  revenue analytics, forecasting, voice of customer).
type: software
authors:
